com.hcl.domino.runtime

Interface DominoRuntime


  • public interface DominoRuntime
    Represents the configuration of the running Notes or Domino environment.

    • Method Summary

    • Method Detail

      • getDataDirectory

        Optional<Path> getDataDirectory()
        Retrieves the path of the data directory for the current Notes/Domino runtime.
        Returns:
        an Optional describing a Path representing the data directory on the filesystem, or an empty one if the directory cannot be determined

      • getProgramDirectory

        Optional<Path> getProgramDirectory()
        Retrieves the path of the program directory for the current Notes/Domino runtime.
        Returns:
        an Optional describing a Path representing the program directory on the filesystem, or an empty one if the directory cannot be determined

      • getTempDirectory

        Optional<Path> getTempDirectory()
        Retrieves the path of the temporary-files directory used by the current Notes/Domino runtime.
        Returns:
        an Optional describing a Path representing the temp directory on the filesystem, or an empty one if the directory cannot be determined

      • getViewRebuildDirectory

        Optional<Path> getViewRebuildDirectory()
        Retrieves the path of the directory used by the current Notes/Domino runtime for temporary storage during view rebuilding.
        Returns:
        an Optional describing a Path representing the view-rebuild directory on the filesystem, or an empty one if the directory cannot be determined

      • setProperty

        void setProperty(String propertyName,
                 String value)
        Sets a Notes configuration property to the specified string.

        These properties correspond to notes.ini settings.

        Parameters:
        propertyName - the property to set
        value - the value to set

      • setProperty

        These properties correspond to notes.ini settings.

        Parameters:
        propertyName - the property to set
        value - the value to set

      • getPropertyString

        String getPropertyString(String propertyName)
        Retrieves the value of a Notes configuration property as a string.

        These properties correspond to notes.ini settings.

        Parameters:
        propertyName - the name of the property to get
        Returns:
        the value of the property as a string

      • getPropertyInt

        int getPropertyInt(String propertyName)
        Retrieves the value of a Notes configuration property as an integer. When the property is not set, this returns 0.

        These properties correspond to notes.ini settings.

        Parameters:
        propertyName - the name of the property to get
        Returns:
        the value of the property as an int

      • invokeNSD

        void invokeNSD(Collection<NSDMode> modes)
        Tells the local runtime to run NSD.
        Parameters:
        modes - configuration options for the NSD execution
